Iran's culture ministry on Monday invited foreign  journalists to attend the fifth anniversary of the death of the founder of  Islamic republic, Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Journalists can contact Iranian consular sections abroad to obtain visas  for the 10-day visit from May 31 to June 9, it said.
President Ali Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani is expected to hold a press  conference "probably on June 7," it added.
The 1979 Iranian revolution overthrew the pro-West Shah and swept Khomeini  into power.
